A '''freight scanners''' is a sensor that allows one to determine another ship's freight, shield, and weapons loadouts.  Required equipment [[Freight Scan|freight scanning missions]], the sensor has a maximum range of four kilometers.

It is considered illegal to scan someone's freight unless you have a [[police license]] for the race that owns the sector.

==Encyclopedia Entry==
Pilots whose [[Ships|spaceships]] are equipped with a freight scanner can see exactly what is inside other ships they scan.  Oftentimes this scanner is abused by [[pirates]] before they attack and rob peaceful pilots.

